CSC (compressed sparse column, a.k.a. Harwell-Boeing) format sparse matrix member functions.

int csc_matrix_expand_symmetric_storage ( struct csc_matrix_t *  A  ) 

If the sparse matrix A is stored in a symmetric space-saving format, expands out A so that all the nonzeros ((i,j) and (j,i)) are explicitly stored.

Changes ownership to LIBRARY_DEALLOCATES and the deallocator to the default.

Parameters:
A [IN/OUT] Sparse matrix in CSC format
Returns:
Nonzero if error, else zero.
